Package org.darkimport.omeglespy_z

Interface Summary
NameGenerator NameGenerators are used to get names for strangers/conversants and names for servers.
OmegleSpyConversationListener This listener interface is specifically implemented in mediation type applications.
 

Class Summary
ChatHistoryHelper This abstract class receives various "chat" related notifications.
CommunicationHelper Requests for communication with an external service are passed through this class.
DefaultCommunicationHelper This is the trivial default implementation of the CommunicationHelper .
DefaultConversantNameGenerator This is the default trivial implementation of the NameGenerator used for generating strangers' names.
DefaultFilterHelper A useful implementation of the FilterHelper.
DefaultLogHelper The default trivial implementation of the LogHelper.
DefaultServerNameGenerator The trivial default implementation of the NameGenerator for generating server names.
FilterHelper The FilterHelper is used to filter messages based on certain criteria (determined by the subclass).
LogHelper This LogHelper is used throughout the core library for logging in lieu of establishing a dependency on a logging framework.
OmegleConnection This class represents a single connection to omegle.
OmegleEvent An event generated by an omegle server from an event ping.
OmegleSpyConversationController The entry point into the omeglespy-z application framework for connection mediation.
OmegleSpyConversationCoordinator This class does the work of managing connections, interpreting omegle events and translating OmegleEvents into OmegleSpyEvents and passing the OmegleSpyEvents onto interested OmegleSpyConversationListeners.
OmegleSpyEvent An event that is generated in the mediation-style context to (typically) guide a UI.
RecaptchaHelper Helper class for recaptchas.
 

Enum Summary
LogLevel This enum contains references to some of the common log levels used throughout the most popular logging frameworks.
OmegleEventType This enum consists of all of the possible omegle event types.
